<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12149g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12149g">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12149g"> 149(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Froissard (nonpatriot) / Vincent &mdash; / Joan (patriot)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Vincent vit &agrave; l&apos;&eacute;poque o&ugrave; l&apos;id&eacute;e de patrie commence seulement &agrave; se former. Il s&apos;intercale dans l&apos;histoire entre deux personnages: <mark>Froissard et Jeanne d&apos;Arc, dont l&apos;un est un sans patrie et dont l&apos;autre est l&apos;h&eacute;ro&iuml;ne de tous les patriotes</mark>. <br><font color="green">[Vincent lived at the time when the idea of fatherland was only beginning to develop. He appears in history between two personalities: Froissard and Joan of Arc, one without country and the other the heroine of all patriots.]</font> <small> Matthieu-Maxime Gorce, <a name="STVF" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#STVF"><cite title="source">Saint Vincent Ferrier</cite></a> (1924) 230</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
